      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SASSY SNIPPET (10) has impressed in his last two trials, winning his latest heat earlier this month. Pike was on board there and he sticks with the filly for her debut effort. Looks to have good ability and she can make a winning start to her career. XENTARO (1) resumed in Saturday grade which was a strong race and he looks better suited back to this level. He's a second-up winner in the past and the inside draw should see him close to the speed. Looks a big improver. LINCHPIN (2) has been contesting much stronger races all campaign and now comes back to midweek company. The niggle is the drop back to 1200m, but he was strong when fresh in the Breeders' Classic first-up. Creates plenty of interest. GANGSTER GODDESS (7) comes back to 1200m today which looks a god move. She also drops back in grade now and a better performance is on the cards. TESTY PHAROAH (3) was beaten fresh but he's better than he showed there. Won't be far away.",
